  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nWhen the user accepts a contact request by taping `Add contact` in a chat, the contact request confirmation is never sent if there is a :shh/post error or if the app is disconnected from the network.\r\n\r\n# Implementation\r\n\r\nSimilar to previous work on contact request, the idea is to store if the contact-request-confirmation? has been sent or not and use the :sent signal to update it when sending is successful\r\n\r\n# Acceptance criteria\r\n\r\nTapping add contact when offline or not connected to any peer will accept the contact and the contact request confirmation is sent as soon as the app is reconnected. Can be verified by updating profile before going back online, the contact should see the update as soon as user is reconnected\r\n",
